WEBVTT

00:07.841 --> 00:12.426
JESUS: Lafayette, did you hear anything
I just said?

00:14.932 --> 00:17.924
Sorry for pushing you into the magic
before you were ready.

00:19.019 --> 00:20.304
Thought I was helping you...

00:22.105 --> 00:24.266
...but I was acting
just like my fucking abuelo.

00:28.445 --> 00:30.777
You were right, baby.

00:33.742 --> 00:36.950
This kind of power, it's not meant for us.

00:37.454 --> 00:38.785
It's too strong.

00:39.790 --> 00:41.872
Or we're too weak.

00:44.294 --> 00:47.661
But I swear
to whatever the fuck is out there...

00:47.839 --> 00:53.300
...if you wanna lead a magic-free life
from here on out, I'm all for it.

00:55.305 --> 00:56.761
Hey.

01:00.811 --> 01:02.642
Are you okay in there?

01:04.940 --> 01:05.975
Yes.

01:08.443 --> 01:09.478
Eat your breakfast.

01:09.653 --> 01:14.568
I know it's not fried in pig fat
or whatever secret deliciousness you use...

01:14.783 --> 01:16.319
...but I worked hard on it.

01:26.545 --> 01:29.833
I'll see you after work.

01:37.681 --> 01:38.841
Lafayette?

01:40.726 --> 01:42.637
[SCREAMS]

03:27.874 --> 03:29.489
TARA:
Hey there.

03:29.668 --> 03:30.874
Morning, Sook.

03:32.838 --> 03:34.044
You get any sleep?

03:36.508 --> 03:37.873
No.

03:41.346 --> 03:42.756
My nerves are shot.

03:43.890 --> 03:45.846
After everything we've been through...

03:46.017 --> 03:49.259
...it's a miracle we're not screaming
in a padded room somewhere.

03:54.192 --> 03:55.693
Tara...

03:57.112 --> 03:59.353
...do you think Gran's in heaven?

04:00.866 --> 04:03.903
Well, I've always considered myself
to be an atheist.

04:04.077 --> 04:05.362
But if heaven does exist...

04:05.537 --> 04:09.871
...l'm pretty sure Adele Stackhouse
would be, like, the president of it.

04:10.292 --> 04:12.032
Why you thinking about that, anyway?

04:14.004 --> 04:15.619
Marnie channeled Gran.

04:16.131 --> 04:20.044
Least I think it was her.
She warned me about Antonia.

04:20.218 --> 04:22.049
Told me not to give my heart to Eric.

04:22.220 --> 04:25.053
Well, she did have all the sense
in the family.

04:29.311 --> 04:31.051
This morning...

04:31.229 --> 04:32.935
...I keep feeling like she's here.

04:33.106 --> 04:34.482
You mean watching over you?

04:34.649 --> 04:37.231
No. I mean, like...

04:37.944 --> 04:39.809
..."here" here.

04:41.573 --> 04:44.064
I know it's probably just
some residual weirdness...

04:44.242 --> 04:47.234
...from everything that's been going on...

04:47.412 --> 04:49.903
...but I just can't shake this feeling.

04:50.081 --> 04:51.946
If she was here,
what do you think she'd say?

04:52.125 --> 04:53.410
To be good to each other.

04:54.252 --> 04:55.583
And wear more sunscreen.

04:55.754 --> 04:58.040
And to stop getting into
so much dang trouble.

04:58.215 --> 04:59.250
[LAUGHS]

04:59.841 --> 05:02.924
What are we, like, magnets
for fucking craziness or something?

05:03.094 --> 05:04.300
Lord, I hope not.

05:04.471 --> 05:09.682
Someday, I see myself growing old...

05:10.101 --> 05:13.639
...and sitting on the porch
with my grandbabies on my lap...

05:13.814 --> 05:16.305
...just watching the sunset.

05:16.483 --> 05:19.316
I hope I get to sit on that porch
with you someday.

05:20.612 --> 05:22.443
Me too.

05:31.289 --> 05:32.825
[MAXINE SNIFFLING]

05:35.502 --> 05:38.960
He was a devious little son of a bitch...

05:39.130 --> 05:41.792
...but somewhere in there
he had a good heart.

05:41.967 --> 05:46.085
Not a lot of people got to see that.
l was lucky enough to be one of them.

05:46.304 --> 05:47.965
Well, thank you for coming.

05:48.139 --> 05:50.346
It would have meant a lot to my brother.

05:50.517 --> 05:54.180
He said, "Sam shooting me was
the best thing that ever happened to me...

05:54.354 --> 05:59.644
...Ms. Fortenberry, because it brought me
to you and the Lord."

06:00.819 --> 06:03.401
Sweet boy.

06:05.156 --> 06:08.990
Course, then he stole
a bunch of my clothes and jewelry.

06:09.661 --> 06:12.323
Even a pair of my underpants.

06:12.914 --> 06:15.621
And my favorite church shoes.

06:16.668 --> 06:18.659
Well, I'm sorry.

06:20.005 --> 06:24.044
Nobody taught Tommy how to love
somebody without hurting them.

06:25.010 --> 06:26.841
I let him down that way too.

06:27.637 --> 06:32.006
My guess is nobody taught you neither.

06:32.517 --> 06:35.884
We all do the best we can
with what we got.

06:38.273 --> 06:42.687
I'm gonna bring by one of my
famous pork rind casseroles later.

06:42.861 --> 06:45.193
No. No, don't trouble yourself,
Ms. Fortenberry.

06:45.363 --> 06:47.228
Oh, nonsense.

06:47.407 --> 06:50.649
Tommy may not have been
my flesh and blood...

06:51.077 --> 06:53.568
...but he was a son to me.

06:55.206 --> 06:58.949
You call me Mama from now on.

06:59.169 --> 07:02.081
We're all the family we got left.

07:14.184 --> 07:16.095
[SIGHS]

07:16.269 --> 07:18.009
[SNIFFLING]

07:31.409 --> 07:32.910
Hey.

07:45.131 --> 07:49.090
Jason Stackhouse,
you are a good person.

07:49.260 --> 07:51.091
Yes, you are.

07:52.764 --> 07:54.504
Shutup.

08:07.320 --> 08:10.027
-Hey, Jason.
-Hey, buddy. Heh.

08:11.116 --> 08:12.777
What you doing?

08:13.493 --> 08:16.951
Oh, just working. You know?

08:18.289 --> 08:21.452
-What you doing?
-Just chilling.

08:21.626 --> 08:24.459
You know, it's a nice day.

08:25.338 --> 08:26.748
Um....

08:28.133 --> 08:30.465
It's moist.

08:31.970 --> 08:34.803
-Somebody die?
-No.

08:37.809 --> 08:39.470
Listen, we gotta talk, man.

08:40.854 --> 08:42.594
Uh....

08:44.482 --> 08:45.983
You mind--?

08:46.151 --> 08:48.642
You mind putting that thing down first?

08:51.197 --> 08:52.778
Listen...

08:53.825 --> 08:56.783
...we've been friends a long time.

08:58.329 --> 08:59.865
You remember....

09:00.081 --> 09:01.241
BOTH [IN UNISON]:
om

09:01.416 --> 09:02.826
[CLICKING]

09:03.001 --> 09:04.411
BOTH [IN UNISON]:
Boom, boom.

09:04.586 --> 09:06.201
[BOTH CHUCKLING]

09:09.674 --> 09:11.790
I had sex with Jessica.

09:12.761 --> 09:14.626
[LAUGHS]

09:14.804 --> 09:16.214
You--

09:17.182 --> 09:18.797
I ain't joking.

09:20.018 --> 09:22.851
| wish I was, but I ain't.

09:27.525 --> 09:28.560
How?

09:29.527 --> 09:31.859
Kind of a weird question to ask, man.

09:32.030 --> 09:34.021
But if you really wanna know...

09:34.199 --> 09:38.283
...missionary, then doggie,
then her on top.

09:38.453 --> 09:39.613
I mean, it was nothing too kinky.

09:39.788 --> 09:41.198
[GRUNTS]

09:42.082 --> 09:45.540
No, how could you do that to me?
Not "how did you fuck my girl?"

09:45.710 --> 09:47.371
Listen, I'm sorry, man.

09:48.046 --> 09:51.038
But technically-- Hey, technically,
she wasn't your girl no more.

09:51.216 --> 09:53.548
You said you never wanted
to see her again.

09:53.718 --> 09:55.549
Yeah, fuck you!

09:55.887 --> 09:57.377
We had a code, and you broke it.

09:57.555 --> 10:01.343
You could've had anyone.
Anyone you wanted.

10:02.102 --> 10:03.558
I'm not you, man.

10:03.728 --> 10:06.219
She was the only one.

10:08.900 --> 10:11.141
I drank her blood.

10:12.737 --> 10:14.443
I couldn't think about anything else.

10:15.573 --> 10:18.280
I tried to fight it, but it just happened.

10:18.993 --> 10:20.779
[GRUNTS]

10:21.371 --> 10:23.908
No, it doesn'tjust happen.
You make choices.

10:24.082 --> 10:26.789
You make fucked-up, selfish,
piece-of—shit choices.

10:26.960 --> 10:28.666
[GROANING]

10:29.629 --> 10:32.917
All right. You made your point, Hoyt.

10:34.300 --> 10:35.380
You made your point.

10:35.552 --> 10:37.133
[GRUNTING]

10:37.762 --> 10:41.596
Ain't nothing more important to you
than your dick. Not even your best friend.

10:42.433 --> 10:44.594
What Jess and I had, it was real...

10:44.769 --> 10:48.136
...and you ain't never gonna have that,
not with her, not with anybody...

10:48.314 --> 10:51.647
...because there's something
inside you that's-- It's just missing.

10:57.615 --> 10:59.401
Sorry.

11:09.627 --> 11:11.458
JESUS:
Lafayette.

11:14.299 --> 11:17.132
Lafayette, listen to me.
I know you're in there.

11:17.302 --> 11:21.215
Whatever Marnie's making you do,
you have to fight her.

11:21.389 --> 11:23.004
[CHUCKUNG]

11:26.311 --> 11:30.645
You think your little fry cook
can overpower me?

11:31.232 --> 11:36.147
True, his body is younger and stronger
than mine was...

11:36.321 --> 11:41.657
...and the magic in him is potent.
Clumsy, but potent.

11:43.328 --> 11:44.818
He is no Antonia.

11:44.996 --> 11:49.160
Marnie, before Antonia came along,
you were afraid of your own voice.

11:50.335 --> 11:53.748
You talked to the dead
because they were your only friends.

11:54.672 --> 11:56.833
That's why you wanted possession
so badly...

11:57.008 --> 11:59.670
...because you felt lonely...

12:00.178 --> 12:01.463
...helpless.

12:03.890 --> 12:05.846
I thought you were my friend.

12:06.017 --> 12:08.383
I trusted you.

12:08.561 --> 12:11.769
-And you took her away from me.
-She wanted to leave, Marnie.

12:12.523 --> 12:14.900
Antonia knew you weren't fighting
a righteous war.

12:15.068 --> 12:18.105
She knew that all you really cared about
was power.

12:18.279 --> 12:21.362
You don't deserve to speak her name.
Traitor.

12:22.367 --> 12:25.359
Antonia was a hero. A martyr.

12:25.536 --> 12:28.744
Unlike this Lafayette coward,
whom I've had to take by force.

12:29.874 --> 12:32.581
Jesus, this bitch is strong
and seriously homicidal.

12:34.545 --> 12:38.709
Call me bitch again, boy, and I'll cut out
your eyeball and feed it to you.

12:39.133 --> 12:40.714
I can't feel pain, but you will.

12:40.885 --> 12:42.386
Marnie, please don't hurt him.

12:43.388 --> 12:45.253
I'll do whatever you want.

12:45.431 --> 12:47.547
Just tell me.
Tell me what you want us to do.

12:48.726 --> 12:55.598
I want what your grandfather
passed down to you in the blood...

12:56.818 --> 12:59.776
...what you've been running from
your whole life.

12:59.946 --> 13:04.064
I want your magic, brujo.

13:06.619 --> 13:08.280
All of it.

13:13.376 --> 13:16.914
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYS]

13:17.255 --> 13:19.416
Hey, Arlene. Oh!

13:19.590 --> 13:20.921
Happy Halloween.

13:21.092 --> 13:22.923
Oh, is Halloween today?

13:23.094 --> 13:26.427
ARLENE: Yep.
-Can I interest you in a hand sandwich?

13:26.597 --> 13:27.632
[CACKLING]

13:28.516 --> 13:29.596
[LAUGHS]

13:30.768 --> 13:32.599
We're zombies.

13:32.770 --> 13:35.261
Zombies are the new vampires.
Didn't you know that?

13:35.440 --> 13:39.103
No, I did not know that, but your
severed-toe necklace is super cute.

13:39.277 --> 13:41.313
-Thank you.
-ls Sam around?

13:42.405 --> 13:45.568
ARLENE:
Oh, Lord, nobody’s told her yet.

13:47.994 --> 13:49.950
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

13:51.622 --> 13:53.283
SAM:
Come in.

13:55.001 --> 13:57.037
-Hey.
-Hi.

13:57.211 --> 14:00.954
I'm sorry about Tommy. | just heard.

14:01.132 --> 14:04.295
-The funeral?
-Yeah, well, nobody knew about it.

14:04.469 --> 14:07.211
My brother didn't have
a whole lot of friends around here.

14:07.388 --> 14:08.673
You do.

14:08.848 --> 14:11.681
I hadn't seen you in a while.
Figured you had a lot going on.

14:12.143 --> 14:13.883
Sam.

14:14.145 --> 14:17.478
l was pretty sore
after you fired me and all...

14:18.649 --> 14:21.561
-...but I would've been there for you.
-I never fired you.

14:21.736 --> 14:23.897
You're the one who didn't show up
for shifts.

14:24.113 --> 14:27.150
Not to be a stickler for details...

14:27.658 --> 14:32.322
...but you told me l was nothing but trouble
and to get my stuff and get out of here.

14:36.376 --> 14:39.493
You know what?
I wasn't myself that day.

14:40.213 --> 14:43.000
I'll tell you what. How about
we let bygones be bygones, huh?

14:43.174 --> 14:45.210
Does that mean I can have my job back?

14:45.385 --> 14:47.171
As long as you can start right now.

14:47.345 --> 14:49.427
Lafayette's MIA
and with it being Halloween...

14:49.597 --> 14:51.679
...we sure could use
an extra pair of hands.

14:51.849 --> 14:55.216
Can I have a new uniform?
I kind of threw mine in the trash.

14:55.853 --> 15:00.017
No uniforms today.

15:00.525 --> 15:02.686
-Oh, no.
-Oh, yeah.

15:04.862 --> 15:06.727
You want yourjob back or not?

15:08.032 --> 15:10.648
I'm gonna get you for this, Sam.

15:10.910 --> 15:13.196
SAM:
Nobody likes an angry bunny.

15:14.038 --> 15:18.953
Samhain was Wicca's
greatest holy celebration...

15:19.168 --> 15:21.910
...a night we honored
and communed with our dead.

15:23.047 --> 15:25.038
Now people only know it as Halloween.

15:25.216 --> 15:28.379
Children feed their fat faces
with candy...

15:28.553 --> 15:33.547
...and run in fear
from evil green hags they call witches.

15:34.225 --> 15:40.061
The vampires have done a thorough job
of demonizing our most sacred sabbat...

15:40.731 --> 15:43.313
-...turning our religion into a joke.
-I agree with you.

15:44.527 --> 15:45.562
Vampires suck.

15:47.697 --> 15:51.690
That's why you need to let go of Lafayette
before they find out.

15:53.077 --> 15:54.613
They'll kill him, Marnie.

15:54.787 --> 15:56.823
Just like they killed you.

15:57.290 --> 16:01.829
If you hadn't betrayed me,
I would still be alive.

16:02.003 --> 16:03.618
Besides, it's the only host I have.

16:03.796 --> 16:05.832
He's not a host, he's a person.

16:06.007 --> 16:08.965
With a whole life
and people who love him.

16:09.135 --> 16:11.922
We must all make sacrifices
in time of war.

16:12.346 --> 16:15.588
I made mine,
and now you will make yours.

16:15.766 --> 16:18.724
You can't trade magic
like fucking Pokemon cards.

16:19.979 --> 16:24.018
I would gladly give you this shit
inside of me if I knew how, but I just don't.

16:28.779 --> 16:31.612
-You're afraid.
-Yes.

16:32.366 --> 16:33.617
And you should be too.

16:34.118 --> 16:37.736
Because what's inside of me
is seriously dark.

16:40.124 --> 16:42.115
l'll fight darkness with darkness.

16:42.960 --> 16:46.953
Who are you fighting for, huh?

16:47.131 --> 16:49.338
Antonia's gone, the circle's broken.

16:49.509 --> 16:51.795
They fear you more
than they fear the vampires.

16:51.969 --> 16:55.177
-You've turned into everything you hate.
-Shut up.

16:55.348 --> 16:58.340
Give me what I want,
or I will wring the life out of this body...

16:58.518 --> 17:01.635
...till there is nothing left
but an empty sack.

17:02.146 --> 17:04.979
Okay, enough. Stop it.

17:07.485 --> 17:09.271
I'll do it.

17:12.240 --> 17:14.856
[PANTING]

17:17.411 --> 17:20.778
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

17:31.676 --> 17:33.337
Give it to me.

17:36.514 --> 17:38.004
Give it all to me.

17:39.600 --> 17:41.340
[GROANING]

17:52.154 --> 17:53.234
[GROWLING]

17:55.866 --> 17:57.402
[GROANS]

18:10.756 --> 18:12.542
Lafayette...

18:12.883 --> 18:15.135
...l'm sorry.

18:19.181 --> 18:20.261
[SCREECHES]

18:20.433 --> 18:23.095
ARLENE:
Take off your mask before you eat, now.

18:24.770 --> 18:26.431
Hey, you already had yours.

18:26.606 --> 18:27.971
-l'm eating for two.
ARLENE: Hey.

18:28.149 --> 18:32.734
You start behaving yourselves or you're
gonna be trick-or—treating at the trailer park.

18:32.903 --> 18:35.736
Now, do you want a bag
of empty Coors cans and food stamps...

18:35.906 --> 18:38.613
...or do you want candy?
It is your choice.

18:38.784 --> 18:42.276
Coby, Lisa,
I want you to meet my friend Emma.

18:42.455 --> 18:43.786
-Hi, Emma.
-Hey.

18:43.956 --> 18:46.618
-Hey.
-That's quite a costume you got there, Lisa.

18:46.792 --> 18:50.080
-What are you supposed to be?
-Jenelle from Teen Mom 2.

18:50.630 --> 18:52.120
Don't even get me started.

18:52.757 --> 18:54.338
And what are you, cutie patootie?

18:54.508 --> 18:57.090
I'm either gonna be a shapeshifter
like my mommy...

18:57.261 --> 18:59.252
...or a werewolf like my daddy.

18:59.430 --> 19:00.590
He's dead.

19:00.765 --> 19:03.427
Alrighty, then.
I'm gonna get back to work.

19:09.690 --> 19:11.601
PATRICK:
Private Bellefleur.

19:26.457 --> 19:27.947
I heard you were dead.

19:28.125 --> 19:29.786
I heard you were crazy.

19:29.960 --> 19:33.327
Well, yeah. That's still true.
What the hell you doing in Bon Temps?

19:33.506 --> 19:36.623
Just passing through. Thought I'd
look you up. You look like shit. Ha, ha.

19:36.801 --> 19:38.507
-Yeah, I'm a zombie.
-Uh-huh.

19:38.969 --> 19:42.803
Yeah, but wait till you meet my wife.
Arlene.

19:44.642 --> 19:49.306
Arlene Fowler-Bellefleur, this is Sergeant
Patrick Devins, United States Marine Corps.

19:49.480 --> 19:50.811
The first of the first.

19:50.981 --> 19:52.812
Mrs. Bellefleur, it's an honor.

19:52.983 --> 19:56.851
Well, it's nice to meet you too. Terry's
told me absolutely nothing about you.

19:57.029 --> 19:59.645
Perfect. Then I won't have to lie.

19:59.824 --> 20:01.109
[LAUGHS]

20:01.659 --> 20:04.492
You got time for a drink with a man
whose life you saved?

20:04.995 --> 20:06.030
Twice.

20:16.966 --> 20:19.082
So does this mean
you aren't mad at me anymore?

20:19.260 --> 20:22.673
It's hard staying mad at you.
Especially in those ears.

20:22.847 --> 20:25.259
Sam's idea of payback.

20:25.474 --> 20:28.762
Listen, about the other night,
I should have thanked you.

20:28.978 --> 20:31.845
-I shouldn't have lost it like that.
-I understand why you did.

20:32.022 --> 20:34.308
[HALLOWEEN MUSIC PLAYS]

20:34.859 --> 20:36.599
Where's Debbie?

20:38.195 --> 20:40.277
Oh, Alcide.

20:40.865 --> 20:42.071
What happened?

20:42.241 --> 20:44.232
-You were right about her.
-But she changed.

20:44.410 --> 20:47.368
People don't change.
Theyjust find new ways to lie.

20:47.997 --> 20:50.409
I know you don't want to believe that
right now...

20:50.583 --> 20:52.539
...and I didn't come here to lecture you.

20:52.710 --> 20:54.871
Something tells me
you're about to anyway.

20:58.591 --> 21:02.049
You remember when you said
that if you were smart...

21:02.386 --> 21:05.219
...you would have fallen in love
with someone like me?

21:05.389 --> 21:06.720
Alcide, don't.

21:07.308 --> 21:09.139
People always say follow your heart.

21:10.227 --> 21:14.095
What if your heart keeps telling you to do
the same stupid shit over and over again?

21:16.817 --> 21:18.899
What if our hearts can't be trusted?

21:19.570 --> 21:22.027
If it's our brains
we should be listening to?

21:22.740 --> 21:25.231
You're hurt and angry right now.

21:25.409 --> 21:27.445
-| get it. I've been there.
-No.

21:27.620 --> 21:28.655
I'm seeing clearly.

21:29.580 --> 21:31.241
Debbie's out of my life.

21:31.415 --> 21:33.246
For good this time.

21:33.417 --> 21:34.918
I'm done with the drama.

21:37.671 --> 21:39.286
I want you to be done with it too.

21:39.465 --> 21:41.626
I can't change who I love.

21:43.260 --> 21:45.091
Lord knows I've tried.

21:46.972 --> 21:48.303
Then try harder.

21:53.187 --> 21:55.223
[CELL PHONE RINGS AND BUZZES]

22:01.654 --> 22:03.269
Herveaux.

22:04.281 --> 22:05.782
Where?

22:08.118 --> 22:09.369
You sure?

22:11.330 --> 22:13.321
I'll be there as soon as I can.

22:17.002 --> 22:19.288
-I gotta go.
-Anything I can do?

22:20.297 --> 22:21.628
Just think about what I said.

22:22.800 --> 22:25.963
-And try not to get yourself killed.
-|'|| work on that.

22:31.809 --> 22:32.969
TARA:
Lafayette?

22:33.978 --> 22:35.889
Jesus?

22:36.146 --> 22:38.398
Anybody here?

22:44.154 --> 22:45.815
Hello?

22:49.660 --> 22:51.491
Lafayette?

22:52.746 --> 22:53.781
[GASPS]

22:53.956 --> 22:55.412
[SCREAMS]

23:01.046 --> 23:02.252
[GASPS]

23:02.840 --> 23:05.047
Hey, Sookie.
Can I borrow that lighter?

23:05.217 --> 23:07.503
Holly, you scared the bejesus out of me.

23:08.512 --> 23:10.013
I'm just a fairy, honey.

23:10.180 --> 23:11.761
Ain't nothing scary about fairies.

23:11.932 --> 23:13.217
Yeah, right.

23:15.019 --> 23:16.134
You don't mind, do you?

23:18.439 --> 23:21.852
Halloween makes me kind ofjumpy too.
Always has.

23:24.862 --> 23:27.774
Wiccans, we call it Samhain...

23:28.198 --> 23:30.575
...or the Witches' New Year.

23:32.202 --> 23:36.866
It's the day that the veil between
the living and the dead is at its thinnest.

23:37.041 --> 23:40.033
Can just feel it in the air, you know?

23:43.380 --> 23:45.245
-Want a puff?
-No, thanks.

23:45.424 --> 23:48.040
When I'm high,
I can't shut out the thoughts at all.

23:48.218 --> 23:50.425
It's like the whole world's
screaming at me.

23:50.596 --> 23:53.212
Oh, see, it calms my nerves.

23:53.390 --> 23:55.096
Mother Earth's Valium.

23:56.393 --> 24:01.729
So all day, Ijust had this terrible feeling
in my gut, you know, this dread?

24:02.733 --> 24:06.066
I'm sure it's just a hangover from everything
that happened with Marnie.

24:06.236 --> 24:08.727
I've had the same feeling.

24:12.743 --> 24:13.983
Tara?

24:14.411 --> 24:17.244
-Tara, what is it? What happened?
-She's back.

24:17.414 --> 24:19.405
-Who's back, honey?
-Marnie.

24:19.583 --> 24:21.744
How's that possible?
She died in front of us.

24:21.919 --> 24:23.830
She killed Jesus.

24:24.004 --> 24:25.995
I think she's inside Lafayette.

24:32.596 --> 24:33.927
SOOKIE:
Okay, thanks, Ginger.

24:34.932 --> 24:37.139
Ginger says Eric's been missing
since nightfall.

24:37.309 --> 24:40.346
-Bill?
-Not answering his phone.

24:40.854 --> 24:42.435
I knew it was in here somewhere.

24:42.606 --> 24:44.267
You carry salt in your purse?

24:44.441 --> 24:47.274
Yeah, and sage
and a lock of my Aunt Josie's hair.

24:47.444 --> 24:49.355
It's like a Wiccan first aid kit.

24:49.530 --> 24:51.612
Hey, any of you two got a mirror?

24:53.242 --> 24:55.483
-Thanks.
-You ever done anything like this before?

24:55.953 --> 24:57.284
Goddess, no.

24:57.454 --> 24:59.991
Usually, I just light a candle
and ask the spirits...

25:00.165 --> 25:03.953
...to make sure my boys don't end up
in jail or knock somebody up...

25:04.128 --> 25:08.713
-...but so far, that's worked out okay.
-Sook, you can't let them hurt him.

25:08.882 --> 25:12.500
If Bill and Eric find out
Marnie's inside Lafayette...

25:13.178 --> 25:15.169
l have a feeling they already know.

25:27.192 --> 25:30.229
Any idea how to get us out of this one,
Your Majesty?

25:30.404 --> 25:33.988
-You could summon Pam.
-You could summon Jessica.

25:34.658 --> 25:39.823
Oh, so you'd sacrifice my progeny,
but not your own?

25:39.997 --> 25:42.659
How very un-kingly of you.

25:43.167 --> 25:46.409
I liked you better
when you were brain-damaged.

25:46.837 --> 25:48.077
-SooMe.
-SooMe.

25:52.926 --> 25:58.671
As your friend Lafayette would say,
what goes around comes around, bitches.

25:58.849 --> 26:00.339
Lafayette.

26:01.018 --> 26:03.350
And Marnie. Please don't do this.

26:03.520 --> 26:07.058
After all they've done to you,
you protect them.

26:07.232 --> 26:10.690
Killing Bill and Eric
isn't gonna make any of that go away.

26:11.195 --> 26:13.026
Revenge will never bring you peace.

26:13.405 --> 26:17.865
There can't be peace
until there is justice for me...

26:18.327 --> 26:23.572
...for Antonia, for all the women
you tortured and burned for centuries.

26:23.749 --> 26:28.209
All to repress a magic that's older and
more powerful than your very existence.

26:28.378 --> 26:30.414
[WHISPERING] Sink all evil
Sink it to the ground thrice

26:30.589 --> 26:33.046
Marnie, what will this serve?

26:33.342 --> 26:36.880
There are millions of us,
more being made every night.

26:37.054 --> 26:38.214
You cannot win.

26:38.388 --> 26:42.597
I'm already dead, vampire.
Thanks to you, I have nothing left to lose.

26:44.228 --> 26:47.391
lncendia of sanctimonia

26:47.564 --> 26:48.974
No!

26:49.149 --> 26:50.389
[SCREAMS]

26:51.610 --> 26:54.977
-Sookie! It's still Lafayette.
-| can'tjust stand here and let them die.

26:56.031 --> 26:57.532
[GRUNTS]

26:59.284 --> 27:00.694
[GROWLS]

27:00.911 --> 27:02.276
[SCREAMS]

27:02.871 --> 27:04.486
No!

27:04.706 --> 27:06.697
[BOTH GROANING]

27:07.751 --> 27:09.582
Give me your hands. Now.

27:09.753 --> 27:11.084
[GROWLS]

27:11.255 --> 27:12.415
I'm sorry, Lafayette.

27:13.257 --> 27:17.341
Spirits who watch over us, friends
Family, ancestors, guardians of the gate

27:17.511 --> 27:18.671
ALL [IN UNISON]:
Spirits who watch over us

27:18.846 --> 27:21.758
Friends, family, ancestors
Guardians of the gate

27:22.933 --> 27:24.139
[GROWLS]

27:24.309 --> 27:25.594
ALL [IN UNISON]:
With this rite we evoke thee

27:25.769 --> 27:27.885
Through the veil of Samhain
We call thee forth

27:28.063 --> 27:30.600
Through the veil of Samhain
We call thee forth

27:30.774 --> 27:33.937
Spirits who watch over us, friends
Family, ancestors, guardians of the gate

27:34.111 --> 27:38.445
Spirits who watch over us, friends
Family, ancestors, guardians of the gate

27:45.873 --> 27:48.159
[BOTH SCREAMING]

27:50.002 --> 27:53.290
Eric, Bill, don't you die on me.

27:53.463 --> 27:55.954
WOMAN: Marnie.
MAN: Marnie.

28:00.470 --> 28:02.426
Marnie.

28:04.558 --> 28:06.514
My sister.

28:06.685 --> 28:08.471
You came back to me.

28:09.813 --> 28:10.973
I knew you would.

28:11.148 --> 28:13.104
[BILL & ERIC SCREAMING]

28:14.985 --> 28:16.145
Antonia, no!

28:18.947 --> 28:22.189
All creatures have their purpose,
even vampires.

28:22.367 --> 28:24.232
How can you say that?
They murdered us.

28:24.453 --> 28:28.321
Their cruelty served its purpose:
to bring you and I together.

28:28.498 --> 28:30.875
And now I am here to take you home.

28:31.835 --> 28:34.497
-I'm not finished yet.
-Oh, yes, you are.

28:35.464 --> 28:38.001
-Gran?
-Holy Goddess.

28:38.175 --> 28:39.711
Holy shit.

28:43.972 --> 28:45.178
TARA:
Lafayette!

28:45.349 --> 28:46.885
[GRUNTS]

28:49.019 --> 28:54.104
I don't want to go. I am not ready.

28:54.274 --> 28:55.514
Please.

28:55.692 --> 28:59.685
l was trapped between worlds
for 400 years...

28:59.863 --> 29:03.697
...lost and driven mad by my rage.

29:03.867 --> 29:05.573
I do not want that for you.

29:05.786 --> 29:08.994
And what about what I want?

29:09.373 --> 29:13.082
Nobody cares what I want.

29:13.752 --> 29:17.586
All my life, I've been afraid.

29:17.756 --> 29:19.542
And who wouldn't be?

29:19.716 --> 29:22.958
With dead people murmuring
in my ears...

29:23.136 --> 29:26.003
...who are making me deliver
your messages...

29:26.890 --> 29:29.381
...making me into a freak.

29:29.559 --> 29:34.724
A creepy, pathetic, terrified mess,
muttering to herself in the corner.

29:34.898 --> 29:37.560
-But that is not who you are anymore.
MARNIE: No.

29:37.734 --> 29:38.940
That's right.

29:39.111 --> 29:41.397
I'm not afraid anymore.

29:42.406 --> 29:45.273
I've got real power now.

29:46.743 --> 29:49.530
And you want to take that away
from me?

29:51.123 --> 29:53.239
You want them to win?

29:53.417 --> 29:55.578
Oh, Marnie.

29:57.254 --> 29:59.586
Marnie, can't you see?

29:59.756 --> 30:02.247
Life is pain.

30:02.426 --> 30:08.092
But soon all you have suffered and feared
will be meaningless.

30:08.265 --> 30:10.301
You will be at peace.

30:11.226 --> 30:12.261
But them....

30:16.940 --> 30:19.147
They'll be stuck here.

30:19.359 --> 30:21.145
Forever.

30:22.070 --> 30:24.152
And there is no victory in that.

30:44.384 --> 30:46.375
[SCREAMS]

30:47.179 --> 30:48.794
That's right, honey.

30:48.972 --> 30:54.808
Let it all out, because there's no room
for that where we're going.

30:54.978 --> 30:57.515
Oh, this fucking sucks.

30:57.981 --> 30:59.357
Change is hard.

31:02.652 --> 31:03.937
[SIGHS]

31:11.661 --> 31:13.117
Gran?

31:18.168 --> 31:19.328
Please don't go.

31:19.878 --> 31:22.494
GRAN:
l have to, dear.

31:22.672 --> 31:25.414
I'm so lost without you.

31:25.634 --> 31:27.875
I don't know what to do.

31:28.053 --> 31:30.169
Yes, you do.

31:30.347 --> 31:33.680
Answer's where it always is,
in your heart.

31:35.519 --> 31:39.182
Being alone, it ain't nothing
to be afraid of, my Sookie.

31:39.648 --> 31:41.855
We're all alone at the end.

31:48.323 --> 31:51.907
[CRYING]

31:57.374 --> 31:59.365
TARA:
Lafayette.

32:00.043 --> 32:02.455
Lafayette, can you hear me?

32:04.089 --> 32:06.205
Bitch, talk to me.

32:06.466 --> 32:07.706
[COUGHS]

32:07.884 --> 32:09.385
TARA:
You're okay.

32:09.553 --> 32:11.714
-You're gonna be Okay.
ERIC: Excuse me.

32:13.223 --> 32:15.965
We're feeling a little crispy up here.

32:17.102 --> 32:20.060
Okay, now I'll bus the tables,
pour the drinks...

32:20.230 --> 32:22.721
...serve the food
and take out the damn garbage.

32:22.899 --> 32:24.890
You know, no problem.

32:25.068 --> 32:29.061
Because, you know, clearly,
I'm the only one who works here anymore.

32:29.239 --> 32:30.900
Flaky skanks.

32:31.074 --> 32:34.111
RENE:
Oh, Lord, ain't you a sight for sore eyes.

32:34.286 --> 32:35.366
[ARLENE GASPS]

32:36.079 --> 32:37.319
Oh, God.

32:37.497 --> 32:40.580
This is a dream. This ain't real.

32:40.750 --> 32:44.208
Okay, wake up, Arlene. Okay.

32:44.629 --> 32:46.244
Wake up.

32:46.423 --> 32:47.458
Ow.

32:47.632 --> 32:49.008
I ain't gonna hurt you, cher.

32:50.302 --> 32:51.587
I loved you, me.

32:52.971 --> 32:55.587
-You and our baby.
-Oh, God.

32:55.765 --> 32:58.507
[SINGING]

33:00.812 --> 33:03.269
Praise Jesus.

33:04.065 --> 33:07.273
-Ah!
-I'm here to warn you, girl.

33:07.444 --> 33:10.026
That man, he's bringing trouble
of the worst kind.

33:11.281 --> 33:12.862
-Terry?
-Mm-hm.

33:13.033 --> 33:14.648
No.

33:14.826 --> 33:17.442
He's good to me and my babies.

33:18.163 --> 33:20.279
I've met the ghosts of his past.

33:21.875 --> 33:25.038
-They ain't gonna rest forever.
TERRY: Arlene.

33:25.253 --> 33:26.959
-Run.
TERRY: What's going on?

33:27.130 --> 33:29.041
-You hear me? Run!
-Ah!

33:35.222 --> 33:36.678
[PANTING]

33:36.848 --> 33:38.304
-You all right?
-Oh, God.

33:38.475 --> 33:41.057
Jesus. Something scare you?

33:45.649 --> 33:47.640
Terry's here now.

33:47.817 --> 33:49.978
Ain't nothing gonna get you.

34:16.555 --> 34:18.045
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

34:18.223 --> 34:20.339
I ain't got no candy.

34:20.517 --> 34:25.728
You little shits egg my house again,
I will arrest you.

34:31.194 --> 34:32.354
JESSICA:
Jason?

34:32.529 --> 34:33.860
What happened to your face?

34:35.115 --> 34:36.230
Is this another dream?

34:37.033 --> 34:41.367
Because if Hoyt pops out from under that
hood, I'm gonna knock him the fuck out.

34:41.871 --> 34:42.906
You told him?

34:43.123 --> 34:44.329
[SIGHS]

34:44.541 --> 34:45.951
Yeah, I told him.

34:48.837 --> 34:50.043
He took it pretty well.

34:53.466 --> 34:55.047
Did you hurt him?

34:56.469 --> 34:57.879
I didn't touch him.

35:04.853 --> 35:06.389
Invite me in.

35:12.235 --> 35:14.396
[MOANING]

35:28.460 --> 35:31.076
I don't wanna be your girlfriend.

35:34.132 --> 35:35.588
What?

35:36.176 --> 35:39.168
| just got out of a serious relationship.

35:39.763 --> 35:42.800
My first and only relationship. I just--

35:43.475 --> 35:45.887
I'm not ready to commit to you.

35:46.811 --> 35:48.767
Okay.

35:48.938 --> 35:50.769
Okay.

35:52.901 --> 35:57.520
Kind of wish you would have told me that
before I took an ass kicking.

35:59.282 --> 36:01.147
I didn't ask you to do that.

36:01.326 --> 36:02.941
No.

36:03.620 --> 36:05.326
But it was the right thing to do.

36:05.497 --> 36:10.958
And since when is Jason Stackhouse
concerned with doing the right thing?

36:14.631 --> 36:17.043
You don't know me very well.

36:24.224 --> 36:25.464
Fair enough.

36:25.642 --> 36:27.803
I'm just barely getting to know myself.

36:27.977 --> 36:31.640
But I don't want to hurt you
the way I hurt Hoyt.

36:34.484 --> 36:36.645
So I'm asking you...

36:37.320 --> 36:39.697
...can this be enough for now?

36:42.158 --> 36:43.819
Becauseun

36:45.036 --> 36:47.027
Because I don't want it to stop.

36:50.750 --> 36:51.990
You know what you are?

36:55.964 --> 36:57.829
You're dangerous.

36:58.550 --> 37:00.165
Yes.

37:01.010 --> 37:02.170
lam.

37:14.899 --> 37:17.276
[MOANING]

37:21.114 --> 37:24.402
-Where the fuck is he?
-I don't know.

37:24.868 --> 37:27.780
-But Sookie called looking for him.
-SooMe.

37:27.996 --> 37:32.365
I am so over Sookie
and her precious fairy vagina...

37:32.542 --> 37:35.534
...and her unbelievably stupid name.

37:35.712 --> 37:37.703
Fuck Sookie.

37:39.299 --> 37:40.334
[PAM SCREAMS]

37:42.135 --> 37:45.252
I've been with Eric over a hundred years.

37:45.430 --> 37:47.967
I've watched him seduce supermodels
and princesses...

37:48.141 --> 37:51.474
...and spit out their bones
when he was finished.

37:51.644 --> 37:56.388
How can someone named Sookie
take him away from me?

37:58.234 --> 38:00.611
[SOBBING]

38:04.574 --> 38:07.236
Don't fucking touch me.

38:23.343 --> 38:24.833
Try and get some rest.

38:25.053 --> 38:26.418
I killed him.

38:26.596 --> 38:28.928
No, you didn't.

38:29.098 --> 38:30.258
It wasn't you.

38:30.809 --> 38:34.597
You hear me, Lafayette?
None of this was your fault.

38:34.979 --> 38:36.685
I fucking love you.

38:37.273 --> 38:41.937
We're gonna get through this shit together,
just like we got through everything else.

38:43.279 --> 38:44.985
Okay?

38:48.284 --> 38:50.696
I'll be right out there if you need me.

38:52.247 --> 38:54.613
[LAFAYETTE SNIFFLING]

39:21.901 --> 39:23.641
Does it hurt?

39:25.822 --> 39:28.234
If you want us to stop....

39:31.786 --> 39:34.778
[GASPING]

39:37.500 --> 39:41.834
Okay, I think that's enough.

39:53.224 --> 39:54.509
You saved my life.

39:56.352 --> 39:57.853
Both our lives.

39:58.021 --> 39:59.227
[LAUGHS]

39:59.439 --> 40:00.770
It was my turn.

40:01.524 --> 40:03.060
Thank you.

40:03.902 --> 40:06.063
You don't have to thank me.

40:06.237 --> 40:08.569
I can't imagine a world without you in it.

40:09.741 --> 40:10.856
Both of you.

40:18.458 --> 40:20.870
I can't stand this anymore.

40:22.420 --> 40:24.206
It's like being ripped in half.

40:24.380 --> 40:27.417
No matter what I do,
somebody I love gets hurt.

40:32.555 --> 40:34.386
Sookie, Ijust want for you to be happy.

40:35.600 --> 40:38.888
And if being with Eric
is what makes you happy...

40:39.812 --> 40:41.222
...then you have my blessing.

40:44.400 --> 40:45.480
ERIC:
See?

40:46.945 --> 40:49.732
It's okay, Sookie. Bill's fine with it.

40:51.574 --> 40:53.610
Bill had his chance.

40:53.785 --> 40:55.241
He blew it.

40:55.411 --> 40:57.493
-He lied to you.
-To protect me.

40:57.705 --> 41:01.243
And I lied to him to protect you, and you
lied to both of us so many times...

41:01.417 --> 41:03.248
...we can't count.

41:03.419 --> 41:04.625
What a mess.

41:10.760 --> 41:12.125
I forgive you.

41:13.096 --> 41:16.088
I know you've loved me
every bit as much as I've loved you...

41:16.849 --> 41:19.761
...and we've both hurt each other
just as deeply.

41:20.770 --> 41:22.510
I hope you can forgive me.

41:24.774 --> 41:26.605
SooMe.

41:27.986 --> 41:30.102
Like l have a choice.

41:31.739 --> 41:32.990
You're the love of my life.

41:34.283 --> 41:35.363
I know.

41:36.327 --> 41:38.943
And thatjust makes this harder.

41:48.297 --> 41:53.633
If I'm really honest, it wasn'tjust
goofy, innocent Eric I fell for.

41:54.637 --> 41:59.552
As vicious and untrustworthy
as you can be...

41:59.767 --> 42:02.634
...there's a goodness in you
that breaks my heart...

42:02.812 --> 42:05.474
...because a part of me
has always wanted you.

42:07.984 --> 42:10.270
You won't be sorry.

42:11.195 --> 42:13.481
I already am.

42:14.407 --> 42:19.367
The time we had together
was unforgettable, but it's over.

42:19.579 --> 42:22.070
No, it doesn't have to be.

42:23.541 --> 42:25.577
There is only one way I see this ending...

42:26.169 --> 42:28.831
...and it's me walking away
with neither of you.

42:29.005 --> 42:30.870
-Dontdothb.
-SooMe.

42:31.049 --> 42:36.339
This is the hardest decision
I've ever had to make...

42:36.512 --> 42:39.003
...but I know it's the right one
for all of us.

42:39.432 --> 42:43.425
And so please, don't try to stop me...

42:44.353 --> 42:46.435
...either of you.

43:05.500 --> 43:07.456
[CRYING]

43:15.635 --> 43:17.250
[GASPS]

43:17.428 --> 43:18.804
[FLUTTERING]

43:20.389 --> 43:22.220
Jesus?

43:23.893 --> 43:25.633
Is that you?

43:32.902 --> 43:35.109
Oh, fuck, baby.

43:35.404 --> 43:38.988
Look at you. Look what I did. I'm--

43:39.158 --> 43:40.273
I'm sorry.

43:42.078 --> 43:43.113
Don't worry about it.

43:43.913 --> 43:47.155
What you mean, don't worry about it?
I killed you.

43:47.375 --> 43:49.741
Everything's temporary.

43:50.670 --> 43:53.161
Anyway, I probably would've
gotten cancer...

43:53.381 --> 43:56.919
...died in a bed somewhere with a nurse
who doesn't know the shit I know...

43:57.093 --> 43:59.254
...screwing up my IVs
and giving me bedsores.

44:01.264 --> 44:02.754
I'm cool with how things went.

44:02.932 --> 44:04.422
Well, I sure the fuck ain't.

44:05.601 --> 44:07.262
l murdered the man I love.

44:07.436 --> 44:10.269
How am I supposed to live with that?

44:12.108 --> 44:14.690
Just keep breathing, baby.

44:23.452 --> 44:24.612
It's that simple.

44:29.167 --> 44:30.782
Jesus, wait.

44:31.169 --> 44:32.659
Don't leave me.

44:32.837 --> 44:34.702
Dude, I'm dead.

44:35.131 --> 44:36.962
You're a medium.

44:37.675 --> 44:39.836
I'll always be with you.

44:48.019 --> 44:50.385
[CRYING]

44:56.360 --> 44:58.146
Ms. Cleary.

44:59.864 --> 45:02.822
Happy Halloween, Sheriff Bellefleur.

45:02.992 --> 45:04.482
Andy.

45:06.662 --> 45:09.745
Sorry about the last time
when I took your flowers.

45:09.957 --> 45:11.663
That's okay.

